{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "CloudChemistryFixedpH",
    "description": "Simplified cloud chemistry system with pH as an externally prescribed input parameter \u2014 Seinfeld & Pandis (2006), Ch. 7. Instead of computing pH from the electroneutrality condition (as in the full CloudChemistry model), this variant takes pH_input as an input and derives H_plus = C_ref \u00d7 10^(-pH_input). This is useful for sensitivity studies that vary pH, for cases where unmeasured ions affect pH, or for quick calculations that bypass the full equilibrium solve. The model composes seven aqueous-equilibrium subsystems (WaterEquilibrium, CO2Equilibria, SO2Equilibria, NH3Equilibria, HNO3Equilibria, H2O2Equilibria, O3Equilibria) and the SulfateFormation oxidation kinetics module (O3, H2O2, and Fe/Mn-synergism pathways). All equilibria use van't Hoff temperature dependence from Table 7.4. Migrated from Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb src/cloud_chemistry.jl:269.",
    "tags": [
      "aerosol",
      "cloud_chemistry",
      "aqueous_phase",
      "seinfeld_pandis_ch7",
      "pH_input",
      "fixed_pH",
      "sulfate_formation",
      "composed"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "Aerosol.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-l5r)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, John Wiley & Sons. Chapter 7: Chemistry of the Atmospheric Aqueous Phase. Key sections: \u00a77.3 (aqueous equilibria, Eqs. 7.10\u20137.61 and Table 7.4), \u00a77.4 (rate conversions, Eqs. 7.75\u20137.78), \u00a77.5 (S(IV) oxidation kinetics, Eqs. 7.79\u20137.102)."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "CloudChemistryFixedpH": {
      "reference": {
        "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, John Wiley & Sons, Chapter 7.",
        "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb636b22f2425460e9ed5cba50793bfee1:src/cloud_chemistry.jl:269\n\nUpstream `CloudChemistryFixedpH` (default instance name `:CloudChemFixedpH`) is the simplified variant of CloudChemistry where pH is prescribed rather than solved from electroneutrality. It instantiates eight subsystems: water_eq (WaterEquilibrium), co2_eq (CO2Equilibria), so2_eq (SO2Equilibria), nh3_eq (NH3Equilibria), hno3_eq (HNO3Equilibria), h2o2_eq (H2O2Equilibria), o3_eq (O3Equilibria), and sulfate (SulfateFormation). The SulfateFormation subsystem itself contains five sub-subsystems (o3_ox, h2o2_ox, fe_ox, mn_ox, femn_ox). This ESM uses the ESS spec \u00a74.7 subsystem-composed model pattern, nesting SulfateFormation's subsystems under the `sulfate` subsystem block.\n\nRe-typing: upstream @variables with no governing parent equation (T, pH_input, p_CO2, p_SO2, p_NH3, p_HNO3, p_H2O2, p_O3, Fe_III, Mn_II) and @parameters (L, xi_SO2) migrate as top-level `parameter`s. The one top-level equation H_plus ~ C_ref * 10^(-pH_input) makes H_plus a `state`. In each subsystem, coupled inputs (T, H_plus, p_*) are re-typed from `parameter` to `state` because the parent coupling equations govern their values.\n\nCO2/NH3/HNO3 equilibria are included as subsystems (co2_eq, nh3_eq, hno3_eq) and driven by T, H_plus, and their respective partial pressures, but none of their outputs is aliased to a top-level variable in CloudChemistryFixedpH \u2014 the upstream source code only connects those subsystems' T and H_plus inputs and their respective partial pressures, without aliasing outputs. Their variables are accessible via dotted-path references (e.g., `CloudChemistryFixedpH.co2_eq.HCO3_minus`).\n\nThe R_total sum uses femn_ox.R_FeMn (Eq. 7.102 which already includes Fe-only and Mn-only terms plus the synergistic term) and excludes the standalone fe_ox.R_Fe and mn_ox.R_Mn to avoid double-counting \u2014 matching the upstream comment in sulfate_formation.jl.\n\nH2O2Equilibria and HNO3Equilibria have no standalone `.esm` files on main; their variables and equations are authored directly from the upstream Aerosol.jl @component source (aqueous_equilibria.jl).\n\nTolerance rationale (rel=1e-6): purely algebraic (no ODE integration), closed-form expressions including van't Hoff exp/log factors and polynomial rate laws. rel=1e-6 covers float64 roundoff with headroom, matching the SulfateFormation precedent."
      },
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-06
      },
      "variables": {
        "R_gas": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "J/mol/K",
          "default": 8.31446,
          "description": "Gas constant used in rate-conversion equations. Upstream CloudChemistryFixedpH @constants R_gas = 8.31446 J/mol/K."
        },
        "C_ref": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "default": 1000.0,
          "description": "Reference concentration (1 M = 1000 mol/m\u00b3). Used to derive H_plus from pH_input: H_plus = C_ref \u00d7 10^(-pH_input). Upstream @constants."
        },
        "L": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "g/m^3",
          "default": 0.5,
          "description": "Cloud liquid water content (g m\u207b\u00b3). Default 0.5 g/m\u00b3, a representative stratocumulus value. Passes to the SulfateFormation subsystem for rate-conversion equations (Eqs. 7.75-7.78). Upstream @parameters (no upstream default)."
        },
        "xi_SO2": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1e-09,
          "description": "Gas-phase SO2 mixing ratio (dimensionless mole fraction). Default 1.0e-9 (1 ppb). Used in the SulfateFormation %/hr rate conversion (Eq. 7.76) and SO2 lifetime (Eq. 7.78). Upstream @parameters."
        },
        "T": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "K",
          "default": 298.15,
          "description": "Cloud/air temperature. Drives van't Hoff corrections in all eight subsystems. Default 298.15 K (25\u00b0C). Upstream @variables with no defining parent equation."
        },
        "pH_input": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 4.5,
          "description": "Input pH value (dimensionless). The distinguishing feature of this model variant: pH is prescribed rather than calculated from electroneutrality. H_plus = C_ref \u00d7 10^(-pH_input). Default 4.5, a typical moderately-acidic cloud droplet. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_CO2": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 38.5,
          "description": "Partial pressure of CO2. Default 38.5 Pa \u2248 380 ppm in 1 atm. Drives CO2 dissolution in the co2_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_SO2": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 0.000101325,
          "description": "Partial pressure of SO2. Default 1.01325e-4 Pa = 1 ppb in 1 atm. Drives SO2/S(IV) equilibria in the so2_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_NH3": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 0.000101325,
          "description": "Partial pressure of NH3. Default 1.01325e-4 Pa = 1 ppb. Drives NH3 dissolution and NH4+ formation in the nh3_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_HNO3": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 0.000101325,
          "description": "Partial pressure of HNO3. Default 1.01325e-4 Pa = 1 ppb. Drives HNO3 dissolution in the hno3_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_H2O2": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 0.000101325,
          "description": "Partial pressure of H2O2. Default 1.01325e-4 Pa = 1 ppb. Drives H2O2 dissolution (very soluble) in the h2o2_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "p_O3": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "Pa",
          "default": 0.005066,
          "description": "Partial pressure of O3. Default 5.066e-3 Pa \u2248 50 ppb. Drives O3 dissolution in the o3_eq subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "Fe_III": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "default": 0.001,
          "description": "Fe(III) concentration in the cloud droplet. Default 1.0e-3 mol/m\u00b3 (1 \u00b5M), representative of Fe-containing cloud water. Catalyst for S(IV) oxidation via the Fe/Mn synergism pathway. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "Mn_II": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "default": 0.001,
          "description": "Mn(II) concentration in the cloud droplet. Default 1.0e-3 mol/m\u00b3 (1 \u00b5M), representative of Mn-containing cloud water. Catalyst for S(IV) oxidation via the Fe/Mn synergism pathway. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "H_plus": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Hydrogen ion concentration, derived from the input pH: H_plus = C_ref \u00d7 10^(-pH_input). At pH 4.5: H_plus = 0.0316 mol/m\u00b3. Couples all equilibrium subsystems. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "OH_minus": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Hydroxide concentration, aliased from water_eq.OH_minus = K_w(T) / H_plus. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "SO2_aq": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Aqueous SO2 ([SO2\u00b7H2O]) concentration, aliased from so2_eq.SO2_aq = H_SO2(T) \u00d7 p_SO2. Coupled to the SulfateFormation subsystem. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "HSO3_minus": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Bisulfite [HSO3\u207b] concentration, aliased from so2_eq.HSO3_minus. Dominates the S(IV) system at typical cloud pH (3\u20135). Coupled to SulfateFormation. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "SO3_2minus": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Sulfite [SO3\u00b2\u207b] concentration, aliased from so2_eq.SO3_2minus. Very important for the O3 oxidation pathway due to the large k2 rate constant. Coupled to SulfateFormation. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "H2O2_aq": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Aqueous H2O2 concentration, aliased from h2o2_eq.H2O2_aq = H_H2O2(T) \u00d7 p_H2O2. H2O2 is highly soluble and this is typically large. Coupled to SulfateFormation. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "O3_aq": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Aqueous O3 concentration, aliased from o3_eq.O3_aq = H_O3(T) \u00d7 p_O3. O3 is sparingly soluble. Coupled to SulfateFormation. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "S_IV_total": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3",
          "description": "Total S(IV) concentration (SO2_aq + HSO3_minus + SO3_2minus), aliased from so2_eq.S_IV_total. Used in Fe- and Mn-catalyzed oxidation pathways. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "R_total": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3/s",
          "description": "Total S(IV) oxidation rate, aliased from sulfate.R_total = o3_ox.R_O3 + h2o2_ox.R_H2O2 + femn_ox.R_FeMn. The sum uses the Fe/Mn-synergism rate (femn_ox) which subsumes individual Fe and Mn contributions, avoiding double-counting. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "R_O3": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3/s",
          "description": "S(IV) oxidation rate by O3, aliased from sulfate.o3_ox.R_O3. Eq. 7.79: R_O3 = (k0\u00b7[SO2\u00b7H2O] + k1\u00b7[HSO3\u207b] + k2\u00b7[SO3\u00b2\u207b])\u00b7[O3(aq)]. Increases strongly with pH due to the large k2 for SO3\u00b2\u207b. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "R_H2O2": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3/s",
          "description": "S(IV) oxidation rate by H2O2, aliased from sulfate.h2o2_ox.R_H2O2. Eq. 7.84: R_H2O2 = k\u00b7[H\u207a]\u00b7[H2O2]\u00b7[HSO3\u207b]/(1+K\u00b7[H\u207a]). Relatively pH-independent, often the dominant pathway. Upstream @variables."
        },
        "R_FeMn": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "mol/m^3/s",
          "description": "S(IV) oxidation rate via Fe/Mn synergism, aliased from sulfate.femn_ox.R_FeMn. Eq. 7.102: includes Fe-only, Mn-only, and synergistic (k_FeMn=1e10 M\u207b\u00b2s\u207b\u00b9) terms. Upstream @variables."
        }
      },
      "subsystems": {
        "water_eq": {
          "variables": {
            "T": {
              "type": "state",
              "units": "K",
              "default": 298.15,
              "description": "Temperature"
            },
            "H_plus": {
              "type": "state",
              "units": "mol/m^3",
              "default": 0.1,
              "description": "Hydrogen ion concentration (1e-4 mol/m\u00b3 = pH 7 in pure water at 298 K)"
            },
            "R_gas": {
              "type": "parameter",
              "units": "J/mol/K",
              "default": 8.314,
              "description": "Gas constant"
            },
            "T_ref": {
              "type": "parameter",
              "units": "K",
              "default": 298.0,
              "description": "Reference temperature"
            },
            "K_w_298": {
              "type": "parameter",
              "units": "mol^2/m^6",
              "default": 1e-08,
              "description": "K_w at 298 K (1.0e-14 M\u00b2 converted to mol\u00b2/m\u2076)"
            },
            "dH_Kw": {
              "type": "parameter",
              "units": "J/mol",
              "default": 55856.4,
              "description": "Enthalpy for K_w (13.35 kcal/mol converted to J/mol; Seinfeld & Pandis Table 7.4)"
            },
            "C_ref": {
              "type": "parameter",
              "units": "mol/m^3",
              "default": 1000.0,
              "description": "Reference concentration (1 mol/L = 1000 mol/m\u00b3) used to convert [H+] from SI to molarity for pH"
            },
            "K_w": {
              "type": "state",
              "units": "mol^2/m^6",
              "description": "Water dissociation constant at temperature T"
            },
            "OH_minus": {
              "type": "state",
              "units": "mol/m^3",
              "description": "Hydroxide ion concentration"
            },
            "pH": {
              "type": "state",
              "units": "1",
              "description": "pH value (dimensionless)"
            }
          },
          "equations": [
            {
              "lhs": "K_w",
              "rhs": {
                "op": "*",
                "args": [
                  "K_w_298",
                  {
                    "op": "exp",
                    "args": [
                      {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                          {
                            "op": "*",
                            "args": [
                              -1,
                              {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                  {
                                    "op": "/",
                                    "args": [
                                      1,
                                      "T"
                                    ]
                                  },
                                  {
                                    "op": "/",
                                    "args": [
                                      -1,
                                      "T_ref"
                                    ]
                                  }
                                ]
                              },
                              "dH_Kw"
                            ]
                          },
                          "R_gas"
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lhs": "K_w",
              "rhs": {
                "op": "*",
                "args": [
                  "H_plus",
                  "OH_minus"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lhs": "pH",
              "rhs": {
                "op": "*",
                "args": [
                  -1,
                  {
                    "op": "log10",
                    "args": [
                      {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
